Just realised though that my `tor`, although it has PoWDefenses compiled in, does not support it via ADD_ONION yet

```bash
 tor --list-modules
relay: yes
dirauth: yes
dircache: yes
pow: yes

 nc 127.0.0.1 9051
AUTHENTICATE ""
250 OK
ADD_ONION NEW:ED25519-V3 PoWDefensesEnabled=1 Port=38333,127.0.0.1:38333
512 Bad arguments to ADD_ONION: Unrecognized keyword argument "PoWDefensesEnabled"
```

I think it might only be for pre-configured services unti [addition to the ONION keyword](https://gitlab.torproject.org/tpo/core/tor/-/raw/main/ChangeLog) in `0.4.9.5`. That said, it does show the fallback mechanism, even in this edge case, works as intended... (and in fact that querying the binary modules would have been a bug here?).
